    "code": "012", 
    "data": "بِسْمِ ٱللَّهِ ٱلرَّحْمَٰنِ ٱلرَّحِيمِ\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nوَٱلَّيْلِ إِذَا يَغْشَىٰ (1) \nI swear by the night when it draws a veil,\nوَٱلنَّهَارِ إِذَا تَجَلَّىٰ (2) \nAnd the day when it shines in brightness,\nوَمَا خَلَقَ ٱلذَّكَرَ وَٱلْأُنثَىٰٓ (3) \nAnd the creating of the male and the female,\nإِنَّ سَعْيَكُمْ لَشَتَّىٰ (4) \nYour striving is most surely (directed to) various (ends).\nفَأَمَّا مَنْ أَعْطَىٰ وَٱتَّقَىٰ (5) \nThen as for him who gives away and guards (against evil),\nوَصَدَّقَ بِٱلْحُسْنَىٰ (6) \nAnd accepts the best,\nفَسَنُيَسِّرُهُۥ لِلْيُسْرَىٰ (7) \nWe will facilitate for him the easy end.\nوَأَمَّا مَنۢ بَخِلَ وَٱسْتَغْنَىٰ (8) \nAnd as for him who is niggardly and considers himself free from need (of Allah),\nوَكَذَّبَ بِٱلْحُسْنَىٰ (9) \nAnd rejects the best,\nفَسَنُيَسِّرُهُۥ لِلْعُسْرَىٰ (10) \nWe will facilitate for him the difficult end.\nوَمَا يُغْنِى عَنْهُ مَالُهُۥٓ إِذَا تَرَدَّىٰٓ (11) \nAnd his wealth will not avail him when he perishes.\nإِنَّ عَلَيْنَا لَلْهُدَىٰ (12) \nSurely Ours is it to show the way,\nوَإِنَّ لَنَا لَلْءَاخِرَةَ وَٱلْأُولَىٰ (13) \nAnd most surely Ours is the hereafter and the former.\nفَأَنذَرْتُكُمْ نَارًا تَلَظَّىٰ (14) \nTherefore I warn you of the fire that flames:\nلَا يَصْلَىٰهَآ إِلَّا ٱلْأَشْقَى (15) \nNone shall enter it but the most unhappy,\nٱلَّذِى كَذَّبَ وَتَوَلَّىٰ (16) \nWho gives the lie (to the truth) and turns (his) back.\nوَسَيُجَنَّبُهَا ٱلْأَتْقَى (17) \nAnd away from it shall be kept the one who guards most (against evil),\nٱلَّذِى يُؤْتِى مَالَهُۥ يَتَزَكَّىٰ (18) \nWho gives away his wealth, purifying himself\nوَمَا لِأَحَدٍ عِندَهُۥ مِن نِّعْمَةٍ تُجْزَىٰٓ (19) \nAnd no one has with him any boon for which he should be rewarded,\nإِلَّا ٱبْتِغَآءَ وَجْهِ رَبِّهِ ٱلْأَعْلَىٰ (20) \nExcept the seeking of the pleasure of his Lord, the Most High.\nوَلَسَوْفَ يَرْضَىٰ (21) \nAnd he shall soon be well-pleased.", 
    "title": "92: Al-Lail الليل"
}